law.text:
Any licensee or employer of a licensee having actual or direct knowledge of facts shall report to the board a behavior analyst or assistant behavior analyst who:
Has been convicted of a felony that involved any act that bears directly on the qualifications or ability of the applicant or licensee to practice behavior analysis;
Is suspected of fraud or deceit in procuring or attempting to procure a license to practice behavior analysis or of negligently performing actions that justify action against a behavior analyst's or assistant behavior analyst's license as identified in KRS 319C.110(2);
Has had a license to practice as a behavior analyst or assistant behavior analyst denied, limited, suspended, probated, or revoked in another jurisdiction on grounds sufficient to cause a license or certificate to be denied, limited, suspended, probated, or revoked in this Commonwealth; or
Is practicing behavior analysis without a current active license issued by the board.
